<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5829171>
    dc:description "Fig. 80. Monoicomyces spp. A–B. M. athetae Thaxt. Ascospores released from perithecia can be seen. A. Mature thallus showing a rudimentary secondary appendage (arrow). B. Mature thallus showing stalk cell of perithecium narrowing and darkening near the base (*) and rounded protuberance on one side of the perithecial tip (arrow). – C. M. bolitocharae T.Majewski. Mature thallus. Scale bars: 50 µm. Photographs from slides ZMUC C-F-123167 (A–B), ZMUC C-F-123746 (C)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5829171/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

